The paper deals with program transformation techniques to reduce the overhead of run time monitoring of contracts. This topic is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) as it aims to improve the performance of software systems. The paper also discusses the propagation and evaluation of contracts, which are concepts related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of security attacks on contracts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a technique to optimize the run time monitoring of contracts, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
